<section>
	<h2>Purpose</h2>
	<p>Provide ability to have a nested field within a checkbox or radio form control.</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Use when</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>An additional optional field is required to gather input from the user; such as an "other" field with a nested "specify".</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Do not use when</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Arbitrarily nest multiple fields.</li>
		<li>Nest multiple levels of fields.</li>
		<li>Nested field is required.</li>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>Working example</h2>
	<p><a href="../../../demos/nested-control/nested-control-en.html">Working example of the nested control css plugin</a></p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>How to implement</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Add the class <code>wb-nested-control</code> to a container element <strong>sibling</strong> to the checkbox or radio button it complements.</li>
		<li>This container element can then have a <code>label</code> and an <code>input</code> of type text for example.</li>
		<li>The <code>wb-nested-control</code> element will be hidden by default. When its associated control is checked, then it displays.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

